  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SRM - Common Commands</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The commands used most often at the <text styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt;</text> prompt. Each <text styleclass="Code Example">show</text> command has its own page in this subsection.</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">show &lt;var&gt; -- display the stored and active value of a console variable.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">set &lt;var&gt; &lt;value&gt; -- change a variable (persisted to NVRAM).</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">show config -- system configuration table (CPU, core logic, memory, PCI / ISA).</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">show device -- enumerated storage / I/O devices.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">show memory -- memory array layout.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">boot -- bootstrap the OS (planned on EmulatR; HALT is the implemented action).</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">help / ? -- console help.</li>
    </list>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
